Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of Four Binary Diethyl Carbonate + 1-Alcohol Systems from (288.15 to 313.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of the binary mixtures of diethyl carbonate (DEC) with ethanol, 1-propanol, 1-pentanol, and 1-octanol were measured over the entire mole fraction at (288.15, 293.15, 303.15, and 313.15) K and normal atmospheric pressure. Moreover, the excess molar enthalpies for the present binary mixtures were determined at 303.15 K. Other mixing properties such as the excess molar volumes have been also obtained for each of the systems and temperatures. The composition viscosity data were correlated with several specific equations to evaluate their suitability for these systems.
